# Version bump required on every change

Before finishing any implementation task that modifies source, config, or scripts:

1. Run `npm run version:build -- --message "concise summary of what changed"` OR rely on the pre-commit hook (`.githooks/pre-commit`) to auto-bump when you commit.
2. Never commit code changes without a corresponding build increment in `version.json`.
3. Updated artifacts (always commit together):
   - `version.json` (build++)
   - `VERSION_LOG.md` (build log entry)
   - `CHANGELOG.md` (`## [Unreleased]` → `### Builds` entry)
   - `build-manifest.json` (structured history)
4. After commit: post-commit hook runs `version:record-commit` and syncs [release-dashboard.canvas.tsx](/Users/RonalSorto/.cursor/projects/Users-RonalSorto-Developer-world-cup/canvases/release-dashboard.canvas.tsx).
5. After deploy: `npm run deploy:vercel` records deploy + syncs canvas.

Semver releases only via `npm run version:patch|minor|major -- --message "..."`.

See [docs/VERSIONING.md](../docs/VERSIONING.md).
